Translate: ‘How many more (enemies) then must Caesar have had, when he made use of their own army to enslave the Roman people?’ Nam is frequently thus used in an elliptical sentence, where the statement, sor which a reason is given, is to be supplied mentally. Cp. 11 5 47, Kritz ad Sall. Iug. xlx 2. The allusion is to Caesar having employed the army raised for the subjugation of Gaul against his own country.
